(1/3)I grew up in an era where people still believed in their government…
(2/3) and saw it as a vehicle through which they could come together and do amazing things for our whole society…
(3/3) like bringing electricity to rural America; like the GI bill; like building the interstate highway system
Disparity is the enemy of community; it separates us; it divides us; it reflects inequality.
We will not succeed in giving all Oregonians greater share of prosperity unless we're willing to have courage, honesty to ? basic fact
Text of Governor Kitzhaber's Historic Fourth Term Inaugural Address http://t.co/6jVV8ynb21
the inherent contradiction between a growing economy & the increasingly desperate plight of hundreds of thousands of our fellow Oregonians
I learned saving the world is a lot harder than it sounds. I have learned it does not happen with a flash of lightning & clap of thunder.
I still believe that all of us want to rise above our own worst day and give something back to our families and to our community.
Let us commit ourselves...to the proposition to ensure every one of us in this great state has an equal opportunity to meet basic needs…
...and to leave their children better off than they were both economically and environmentally.
Although we have made much progress a long road still stretches out before us – and some of us are not going to see the end of that road.
As the father of a 17-yr-old son, I know it is the contributions we make to that future along the way that will matter the most.

Go behind the scenes of the Governor's Office before today's inauguration.
